        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">By examining the molecular structures of D-Glucose and D-Galactose, these two sugars are nearly identical except for the arrangement around a single carbon atom, which classifies them as epimers. Which carbon is responsible for their epimeric relationship?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/03/30/picture13.jpg\" style=\"height:318px; width:300px\" /></span></span></span></p>",
